    <TimeLineElement
      title="4. Liability of Parties"
      subtitle="This section discusses the liability of the Service provider and the User."
    >
      <p><strong>4.1</strong> The Service is provided on an "as is" basis, and the administration shall not be liable for any consequences arising from the use or inability to use the Service.</p>
      <p><strong>4.2</strong> The User fully assumes all risks associated with using the Service, including potential legal consequences for infringing upon third-party rights or violating applicable laws in their country.</p>
    </TimeLineElement>

    <TimeLineElement
      title="5. Compliance with Law"
      subtitle="This section emphasizes legal responsibilities."
    >
      <p><strong>5.1</strong> The User agrees to use the Service in strict compliance with applicable laws in their country.</p>
      <p><strong>5.2</strong> In case of disputes arising from the use of the Service, both parties shall endeavor to resolve them through negotiations; otherwise, disputes shall be subject to resolution in a court located at the place of business of the administration of the Service.</p>
    </TimeLineElement>

